The rain became heavier and heavier as the train moved farther north. The sky was so dark and the windows so steamy that the lanterns were lit by midday. The lunch trolley came rattling along the corridor, and Harry bought a large stack of Cauldron Cakes for them to share.\par
Several of their friends looked in on them as the afternoon pro\-gressed, including Seamus Finnigan, Dean Thomas, and Neville Longbottom, a round-faced, extremely forgetful boy who had been brought up by his formidable witch of a grandmother. Seamus was still wearing his Ireland rosette. Some of its magic seemed to be wearing off now; it was still squeaking \ldblquote\i Troy \emdash  Mullet \emdash  Moran\i0 !\rdblquote  but in a very feeble and exhausted sort of way. After half an hour or so, Hermione, growing tired of the endless Quidditch talk, buried herself once more in \i The Standard Book of Spells, Grade 4,\i0  and started trying to learn a Summoning Charm.\par
Neville listened jealously to the others\rquote  conversation as they re\-lived the Cup match.\par
\ldblquote Gran didn\rquote t want to go,\rdblquote  he said miserably. \ldblquote Wouldn\rquote t buy tick\-ets. It sounded amazing though.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote It was,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote Look at this, Neville. \'85\rdblquote\par
He rummaged in his trunk up in the luggage rack and pulled out the miniature figure of Viktor Krum.\par
\ldblquote Oh \i wow,\i0\rdblquote  said Neville enviously as Ron tipped Krum onto his pudgy hand.\par
\ldblquote We saw him right up close, as well,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote We were in the Top Box \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote For the first and last time in your life, Weasley.\rdblquote\par
Draco Malfoy had appeared in the doorway. Behind him stood Crabbe and Goyle, his enormous, thuggish cronies, both of whom appeared to have grown at least a foot during the summer. Evi\-dently they had overheard the conversation through the compart\-ment door, which Dean and Seamus had left ajar.\par
\ldblquote Don\rquote t remember asking you to join us, Malfoy,\rdblquote  said Harry coolly.\par
\ldblquote Weasley \'85 what is \i that\i0 ?\rdblquote  said Malfoy, pointing at Pigwid\-geon\rquote s cage. A sleeve of Ron\rquote s dress robes was dangling from it, sway\-ing with the motion of the train, the moldy lace cuff very obvious.\par
Ron made to stuff the robes out of sight, but Malfoy was too quick for him; he seized the sleeve and pulled.\par
\ldblquote Look at this!\rdblquote  said Malfoy in ecstasy, holding up Ron\rquote s robes and showing Crabbe and Goyle, \ldblquote Weasley, you weren\rquote t thinking of \i wearing\i0  these, were you? I mean \emdash  they were very fashionable in about eighteen ninety. \'85\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Eat dung, Malfoy!\rdblquote  said Ron, the same color as the dress robes as he snatched them back out of Malfoy\rquote s grip. Malfoy howled with derisive laughter; Crabbe and Goyle guffawed stupidly.\par
\ldblquote So \'85 going to enter, Weasley? Going to try and bring a bit of glory to the family name? There\rquote s money involved as well, you know \'85 you\rquote d be able to afford some decent robes if you won. \'85\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote What are you talking about?\rdblquote  snapped Ron.\par
\ldblquote\i Are you going to enter\i0 ?\rdblquote  Malfoy repeated. \ldblquote I suppose \i you\i0  will, Potter? You never miss a chance to show off, do you?\rdblquote\par
