Through the gates, flanked with statues of winged boars, and up the sweeping drive the carriages trundled, swaying dan\-gerously in what was fast becoming a gale. Leaning against the win\-dow, Harry could see Hogwarts coming nearer, its many lighted windows blurred and shimmering behind the thick curtain of rain. Lightning flashed across the sky as their carriage came to a halt before the great oak front doors, which stood at the top of a flight of stone steps. People who had occupied the carriages in front were already hurrying up the stone steps into the castle. Harry, Ron, Hermione, and Neville jumped down from their carriage and dashed up the steps too, looking up only when they were safely inside the cavernous, torch-lit entrance hall, with its magnificent marble staircase.\par
\ldblquote Blimey,\rdblquote  said Ron, shaking his head and sending water every\-where, \ldblquote if that keeps up the lake\rquote s going to overflow. I\rquote m soak \emdash  ARRGH!\rdblquote\par
A large, red, water-filled balloon had dropped from out of the ceiling onto Ron\rquote s head and exploded. Drenched and sputtering, Ron staggered sideways into Harry, just as a second water bomb dropped \emdash  narrowly missing Hermione, it burst at Harry\rquote s feet, sending a wave of cold water over his sneakers into his socks. Peo\-ple all around them shrieked and started pushing one another in their efforts to get out of the line of fire. Harry looked up and saw, floating twenty feet above them, Peeves the Poltergeist, a little man in a bell-covered hat and orange bow tie, his wide, malicious face contorted with concentration as he took aim again.\par
\ldblquote PEEVES!\rdblquote  yelled an angry voice. \ldblquote Peeves, come down here at ONCE!\rdblquote\par
Professor McGonagall, Deputy Headmistress and head of Gryf\-findor House, had come dashing out of the Great Hall; she skidded on the wet floor and grabbed Hermione around the neck to stop herself from falling.\par
\ldblquote Ouch \emdash  sorry, Miss Granger \emdash\rdblquote\par
