Hagrid was standing outside his hut, one hand on the collar of his enormous black boarhound, Fang. There were several open wooden crates on the ground at his feet, and Fang was whimpering and straining at his collar, apparently keen to investigate the con\-tents more closely. As they drew nearer, an odd rattling noise reached their ears, punctuated by what sounded like minor explosions.\par
\ldblquote Mornin\rquote !\rdblquote  Hagrid said, grinning at Harry, Ron, and Hermione. \ldblquote Be\rquote er wait fer the Slytherins, they won\rquote  want ter miss this \emdash  Blast-Ended Skrewts!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Come again?\rdblquote  said Ron.\par
Hagrid pointed down into the crates.\par
\ldblquote Eurgh!\rdblquote  squealed Lavender Brown, jumping backward.\par
\ldblquote Eurgh\rdblquote  just about summed up the Blast-Ended Skrewts in Harry\rquote s opinion. They looked like deformed, shell-less lobsters, horribly pale and slimy-looking, with legs sticking out in very odd places and no visible heads. There were about a hundred of them in each crate, each about six inches long, crawling over one another, bumping blindly into the sides of the boxes. They were giving off a very powerful smell of rotting fish. Every now and then, sparks would fly out of the end of a skrewt, and with a small \i phut,\i0  it would be propelled forward several inches.\par
\ldblquote On\rquote y jus\rquote  hatched,\rdblquote  said Hagrid proudly, \ldblquote so yeh\rquote ll be able ter raise \rquote em yerselves! Thought we\rquote d make a bit of a project of it!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote And why would we \i want\i0  to raise them?\rdblquote  said a cold voice.\par
The Slytherins had arrived. The speaker was Draco Malfoy. Crabbe and Goyle were chuckling appreciatively at his words.\par
Hagrid looked stumped at the question.\par
\ldblquote I mean, what do they \i do\i0 ?\rdblquote  asked Malfoy. \ldblquote What is the \i point\i0  of them?\rdblquote\par
Hagrid opened his mouth, apparently thinking hard; there was a few seconds\rquote  pause, then he said roughly, \ldblquote Tha\rquote s next lesson, Mal\-foy. Yer jus\rquote  feedin\rquote  \rquote em today. Now, yeh\rquote ll wan\rquote  ter try \rquote em on a few diff\rquote rent things \emdash  I\rquote ve never had \rquote em before, not sure what they\rquote ll go fer \emdash  I got ant eggs an\rquote  frog livers an\rquote  a bit o\rquote  grass snake \emdash  just try \rquote em out with a bit of each.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote First pus and now this,\rdblquote  muttered Seamus.\par
Nothing but deep affection for Hagrid could have made Harry, Ron, and Hermione pick up squelchy handfuls of frog liver and lower them into the crates to tempt the Blast-Ended Skrewts. Harry couldn\rquote t suppress the suspicion that the whole thing was entirely pointless, because the skrewts didn\rquote t seem to have mouths.\par
\ldblquote\i Ouch\i0 !\rdblquote  yelled Dean Thomas after about ten minutes. \ldblquote It got me!\par
Hagrid hurried over to him, looking anxious.\par
\ldblquote Its end exploded!\rdblquote  said Dean angrily, showing Hagrid a burn on his hand.\par
\ldblquote Ah, yeah, that can happen when they blast off,\rdblquote  said Hagrid, nodding.\par
\ldblquote Eurgh!\rdblquote  said Lavender Brown again. \ldblquote Eurgh, Hagrid, what\rquote s that pointy thing on it?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Ah, some of \rquote em have got stings,\rdblquote  said Hagrid enthusiastically (Lavender quickly withdrew her hand from the box). \ldblquote I reckon they\rquote re the males. \'85 The females\rquote ve got sorta sucker things on their bellies. \'85 I think they might be ter suck blood.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Well, I can certainly see why we\rquote re trying to keep them alive,\rdblquote  said Malfoy sarcastically. \ldblquote Who wouldn\rquote t want pets that can burn, sting, and bite all at once?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Just because they\rquote re not very pretty, it doesn\rquote t mean they\rquote re not useful,\rdblquote  Hermione snapped. \ldblquote Dragon blood\rquote s amazingly magical, but you wouldn\rquote t want a dragon for a pet, would you?\rdblquote\par
Harry and Ron grinned at Hagrid, who gave them a furtive smile from behind his bushy beard. Hagrid would have liked nothing better than a pet dragon, as Harry, Ron, and Hermione knew only too well \emdash  he had owned one for a brief period during their first year, a vicious Norwegian Ridgeback by the name of Norbert. Hagrid simply loved monstrous creatures, the more lethal, the better.\par
\ldblquote Well, at least the skrewts are small,\rdblquote  said Ron as they made their way back up to the castle for lunch an hour later.\par
\ldblquote They are \i now,\i0\rdblquote  said Hermione in an exasperated voice, \ldblquote but once Hagrid\rquote s found out what they eat, I expect they\rquote ll be six feet long.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Well, that won\rquote t matter if they turn out to cure seasickness or something, will it?\rdblquote  said Ron, grinning slyly at her.\par
