They sat down at the Gryffindor table and helped themselves to lamb chops and potatoes. Hermione began to eat so fast that Harry and Ron stared at her.\par
\ldblquote Er \emdash  is this the new stand on elf rights?\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote You\rquote re go\-ing to make yourself puke instead?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Hermione, with as much dignity as she could muster with her mouth bulging with sprouts. \ldblquote I just want to get to the library.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote\i What\i0 ?\rdblquote  said Ron in disbelief. \ldblquote Hermione \emdash  it\rquote s the first day back! We haven\rquote t even got homework yet!\rdblquote\par
Hermione shrugged and continued to shovel down her food as though she had not eaten for days. Then she leapt to her feet, said, \ldblquote See you at dinner!\rdblquote  and departed at high speed.\par
When the bell rang to signal the start of afternoon lessons, Harry and Ron set off for North Tower where, at the top of a tightly spiraling staircase, a silver stepladder led to a circular trap\-door in the ceiling, and the room where Professor Trelawney lived.\par
The familiar sweet perfume spreading from the fire met their nostrils as they emerged at the top of the stepladder. As ever, the curtains were all closed; the circular room was bathed in a dim red\-dish light cast by the many lamps, which were all draped with scarves and shawls. Harry and Ron walked through the mass of occupied chintz chairs and poufs that cluttered the room, and sat down at the same small circular table.\par
\ldblquote Good day,\rdblquote  said the misty voice of Professor Trelawney right behind Harry, making him jump.\par
