\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote I was born in July.\rdblquote\par
Ron hastily turned his laugh into a hacking cough.\par
Half an hour later, each of them had been given a complicated circular chart, and was attempting to fill in the position of the planets at their moment of birth. It was dull work, requiring much consultation of timetables and calculation of angles.\par
\ldblquote I\rquote ve got two Neptunes here,\rdblquote  said Harry after a while, frowning down at his piece of parchment, \ldblquote that can\rquote t be right, can it?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Aaaaah,\rdblquote  said Ron, imitating Professor Trelawney\rquote s mystical whisper, \ldblquote when two Neptunes appear in the sky, it is a sure sign that a midget in glasses is being born, Harry \'85\rdblquote\par
Seamus and Dean, who were working nearby, sniggered loudly, though not loudly enough to mask the excited squeals from Laven\-der Brown \emdash  \ldblquote Oh Professor, look! I think I\rquote ve got an unaspected planet! Oooh, which one\rquote s that, Professor?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote It is Uranus, my dear,\rdblquote  said Professor Trelawney, peering down at the chart.\par
\ldblquote Can I have a look at Uranus too, Lavender?\rdblquote  said Ron.\par
Most unfortunately, Professor Trelawney heard him, and it was this, perhaps, that made her give them so much homework at the end of the class.\par
\ldblquote A detailed analysis of the way the planetary movements in the coming month will affect you, with reference to your personal chart,\rdblquote  she snapped, sounding much more like Professor McGona\-gall than her usual airy-fairy self. \ldblquote I want it ready to hand in next Monday, and no excuses!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Miserable old bat,\rdblquote  said Ron bitterly as they joined the crowds descending the staircases back to the Great Hall and dinner. \ldblquote That\rquote ll take all weekend, that will. \'85\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Lots of homework?\rdblquote  said Hermione brightly, catching up with them. \ldblquote Professor Vector didn\rquote t give \i us\i0  any at all!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Well, bully for Professor Vector,\rdblquote  said Ron moodily.\par
They reached the entrance hall, which was packed with people queuing for dinner. They had just joined the end of the line, when a loud voice rang out behind them.\par
\ldblquote Weasley! Hey, Weasley!\rdblquote\par
