When Harry woke up on Sunday morning, it took him a moment to remember why he felt so miserable and wor\-ried. Then the memory of the previous night rolled over him. He sat up and ripped back the curtains of his own four-poster, intend\-ing to talk to Ron, to force Ron to believe him \emdash  only to find that Ron\rquote s bed was empty; he had obviously gone down to breakfast.\par
Harry dressed and went down the spiral staircase into the com\-mon room. The moment he appeared, the people who had already finished breakfast broke into applause again. The prospect of going down into the Great Hall and facing the rest of the Gryffindors, all treating him like some sort of hero, was not inviting; it was that, however, or stay here and allow himself to be cornered by the Creevey brothers, who were both beckoning frantically to him to join them. He walked resolutely over to the portrait hole, pushed it open, climbed out of it, and found himself face-to-face with Hermione.\par
\ldblquote Hello,\rdblquote  she said, holding up a stack of toast, which she was car\-rying in a napkin. \ldblquote I brought you this. \'85 Want to go for a walk?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Good idea,\rdblquote  said Harry gratefully.\par
They went downstairs, crossed the entrance hall quickly without looking in at the Great Hall, and were soon striding across the lawn toward the lake, where the Durmstrang ship was moored, reflected blackly in the water. It was a chilly morning, and they kept moving, munching their toast, as Harry told Hermione exactly what had happened after he had left the Gryffindor table the night before. To his immense relief, Hermione accepted his story without question.\par
\ldblquote Well, of course I knew you hadn\rquote t entered yourself,\rdblquote  she said when he\rquote d finished telling her about the scene in the chamber off the Hall. \ldblquote The look on your face when Dumbledore read out your name! But the question is, who \i did\i0  put it in? Because Moody\rquote s right, Harry \'85 I don\rquote t think any student could have done it \'85 they\rquote d never be able to fool the Goblet, or get over Dumbledore\rquote s \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Have you seen Ron?\rdblquote  Harry interrupted.\par
Hermione hesitated.\par
\ldblquote Erm \'85 yes \'85 he was at breakfast,\rdblquote  she said.\par
\ldblquote Does he still think I entered myself?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Well \'85 no, I don\rquote t think so \'85 not \i really,\i0\rdblquote  said Hermione awkwardly.\par
\ldblquote What\rquote s that supposed to mean, \lquote not \i really\i0\rquote ?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Oh Harry, isn\rquote t it obvious?\rdblquote  Hermione said despairingly. \ldblquote He\rquote s jealous!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote\i Jealous\i0 ?\rdblquote  Harry said incredulously. \ldblquote Jealous of what? He wants to make a prat of himself in front of the whole school, does he?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Look,\rdblquote  said Hermione patiently, \ldblquote it\rquote s always you who gets all the attention, you know it is. I know it\rquote s not your fault,\rdblquote  she added quickly, seeing Harry open his mouth furiously. \ldblquote I know you don\rquote t ask for it \'85 but \emdash  well \emdash  you know, Ron\rquote s got all those brothers to compete against at home, and you\rquote re his best friend, and you\rquote re really famous \emdash  he\rquote s always shunted to one side whenever people see you, and he puts up with it, and he never mentions it, but I suppose this is just one time too many. \'85\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Great,\rdblquote  said Harry bitterly. \ldblquote Really great. Tell him from me I\rquote ll swap any time he wants. Tell him from me he\rquote s welcome to it. \'85 People gawping at my forehead everywhere I go. \'85\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote I\rquote m not telling him anything,\rdblquote  Hermione said shortly. \ldblquote Tell him yourself. It\rquote s the only way to sort this out.\rdblquote\par
