And so they practiced. They didn\rquote t have lunch, but headed for a free classroom, where Harry tried with all his might to make vari\-ous objects fly across the room toward him. He was still having problems. The books and quills kept losing heart halfway across the room and dropping like stones to the floor.\par
\ldblquote Concentrate, Harry, \i concentrate. \'85\i0\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote What d\rquote you think I\rquote m trying to do?\rdblquote  said Harry angrily. \ldblquote A great big dragon keeps popping up in my head for some reason. \'85 Okay, try again. \'85\rdblquote\par
He wanted to skip Divination to keep practicing, but Hermione refused point-blank to skive off Arithmancy, and there was no point in staying without her. He therefore had to endure over an hour of Professor Trelawney, who spent half the lesson telling everyone that the position of Mars with relation to Saturn at that moment meant that people born in July were in great danger of sudden, violent deaths.\par
\ldblquote Well, that\rquote s good,\rdblquote  said Harry loudly, his temper getting the better of him, \ldblquote just as long as it\rquote s not drawn-out. I don\rquote t want to suffer.\rdblquote\par
Ron looked for a moment as though he was going to laugh; he certainly caught Harry\rquote s eye for the first time in days, but Harry was still feeling too resentful toward Ron to care. He spent the rest of the lesson trying to attract small objects toward him under the table with his wand. He managed to make a fly zoom straight into his hand, though he wasn\rquote t entirely sure that was his prowess at Summoning Charms \emdash  perhaps the fly was just stupid.\par
He forced down some dinner after Divination, then returned to the empty classroom with Hermione, using the Invisibility Cloak to avoid the teachers. They kept practicing until past midnight. They would have stayed longer, but Peeves turned up and, pre\-tending to think that Harry wanted things thrown at him, started chucking chairs across the room. Harry and Hermione left in a hurry before the noise attracted Filch, and went back to the Gryffindor common room, which was now mercifully empty.\par
At two o\rquote clock in the morning, Harry stood near the fireplace, surrounded by heaps of objects: books, quills, several upturned chairs, an old set of Gobstones, and Neville\rquote s toad, Trevor. Only in the last hour had Harry really got the hang of the Summoning Charm.\par
\ldblquote That\rquote s better, Harry, that\rquote s loads better,\rdblquote  Hermione said, look\-ing exhausted but very pleased.\par
\ldblquote Well, now we know what to do next time I can\rquote t manage a spell,\rdblquote  Harry said, throwing a rune dictionary back to Hermione, so he could try again, \ldblquote threaten me with a dragon. Right \'85\rdblquote  He raised his wand once more. \ldblquote\i Accio Dictionary\i0 !\rdblquote\par
