Snape and Karkaroff came around the corner. Snape had his wand out and was blasting rosebushes apart, his expression most ill-natured. Squeals issued from many of the bushes, and dark shapes emerged from them.\par
\ldblquote Ten points from Ravenclaw, Fawcett!\rdblquote  Snape snarled as a girl ran past him. \ldblquote And ten points from Hufflepuff too, Stebbins!\rdblquote  as a boy went rushing after her. \ldblquote And what are you two doing?\rdblquote  he added, catching sight of Harry and Ron on the path ahead. Karkaroff, Harry saw, looked slightly discomposed to see them standing there. His hand went nervously to his goatee, and he began winding it around his finger.\par
\ldblquote We\rquote re walking,\rdblquote  Ron told Snape shortly. \ldblquote Not against the law, is it?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Keep walking, then!\rdblquote  Snape snarled, and he brushed past them, his long black cloak billowing out behind him. Karkaroff hurried away after Snape. Harry and Ron continued down the path.\par
\ldblquote What\rquote s got Karkaroff all worried?\rdblquote  Ron muttered.\par
\ldblquote And since when have he and Snape been on first-name terms?\rdblquote  said Harry slowly.\par
They had reached a large stone reindeer now, over which they could see the sparkling jets of a tall fountain. The shadowy out\-lines of two enormous people were visible on a stone bench, watching the water in the moonlight. And then Harry heard Hagrid speak.\par
\ldblquote Momen\rquote  I saw yeh, I knew,\rdblquote  he was saying, in an oddly husky voice.\par
