He knew immediately, from the look Ron was giving him, that he was once again revealing his ignorance of the wizarding world. Brought up by the Dursleys, there were many things that wizards took for granted that were revelations to Harry, but these surprises had become fewer with each successive year. Now, however, he could tell that most wizards would not have said \ldblquote So what?\rdblquote  upon finding out that one of their friends had a giantess for a mother.\par
\ldblquote I\rquote ll explain inside,\rdblquote  said Ron quietly, \ldblquote c\rquote mon. \'85\rdblquote\par
