The golden egg fell through the tapestry at the bottom of the staircase, burst open, and began wailing loudly in the corridor be\-low. Harry pulled out his wand and struggled to touch the Ma\-rauder\rquote s Map, to wipe it blank, but it was too far away to reach \emdash\par
Pulling the cloak back over himself Harry straightened up, lis\-tening hard with his eyes screwed up with fear \'85 and, almost immediately \emdash\par
\ldblquote PEEVES!\rdblquote\par
It was the unmistakable hunting cry of Filch the caretaker. Harry could hear his rapid, shuffling footsteps coming nearer and nearer, his wheezy voice raised in fury.\par
\ldblquote What\rquote s this racket? Wake up the whole castle, will you? I\rquote ll have you, Peeves, I\rquote ll have you, you\rquote ll \'85 and what is this?\rdblquote\par
Filch\rquote s footsteps halted; there was a clink of metal on metal and the wailing stopped \emdash  Filch had picked up the egg and closed it. Harry stood very still, one leg still jammed tightly in the magical step, listening. Any moment now, Filch was going to pull aside the tapestry, expecting to see Peeves \'85 and there would be no Peeves \'85 but if he came up the stairs, he would spot the Ma\-rauder\rquote s Map \'85 and Invisibility Cloak or not, the map would show \ldblquote Harry Potter\rdblquote  standing exactly where he was.\par
\ldblquote Egg?\rdblquote  Filch said quietly at the foot of the stairs. \ldblquote My sweet!\rdblquote  \emdash  Mrs. Norris was obviously with him \emdash  \ldblquote This is a Triwizard clue! This belongs to a school champion!\rdblquote\par
Harry felt sick; his heart was hammering very fast \emdash\par
\ldblquote PEEVES!\rdblquote  Filch roared gleefully. \ldblquote You\rquote ve been stealing!\rdblquote\par
He ripped back the tapestry below, and Harry saw his horrible, pouchy face and bulging, pale eyes staring up the dark and (to Filch) deserted staircase.\par
\ldblquote Hiding, are you?\rdblquote  he said softly. \ldblquote I\rquote m coming to get you, Peeves. \'85 You\rquote ve gone and stolen a Triwizard clue, Peeves. \'85 Dumbledore\rquote ll have you out of here for this, you filthy, pilfering poltergeist. \'85\rdblquote\par
Filch started to climb the stairs, his scrawny, dust-colored cat at his heels. Mrs. Norris\rquote s lamp-like eyes, so very like her master\rquote s, were fixed directly upon Harry. He had had occasion before now to wonder whether the Invisibility Cloak worked on cats. \'85 Sick with apprehension, he watched Filch drawing nearer and nearer in his old flannel dressing gown \emdash  he tried desperately to pull his trapped leg free, but it merely sank a few more inches \emdash  any sec\-ond now, Filch was going to spot the map or walk right into him \emdash\par
\ldblquote Filch? What\rquote s going on?\rdblquote\par
Filch stopped a few steps below Harry and turned. At the foot of the stairs stood the only person who could make Harry\rquote s situation worse: Snape. He was wearing a long gray nightshirt and he looked livid.\par
\ldblquote It\rquote s Peeves, Professor,\rdblquote  Filch whispered malevolently. \ldblquote He threw this egg down the stairs.\rdblquote\par
Snape climbed up the stairs quickly and stopped beside Filch. Harry gritted his teeth, convinced his loudly thumping heart would give him away at any second. \'85\par
\ldblquote Peeves?\rdblquote  said Snape softly, staring at the egg in Filch\rquote s hands. \ldblquote But Peeves couldn\rquote t get into my office. \'85\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote This egg was in your office, Professor?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Of course not,\rdblquote  Snape snapped. \ldblquote I heard banging and wailing \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Yes, Professor, that was the egg \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote\emdash  I was coming to investigate \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote\emdash  Peeves threw it, Professor \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote\emdash  and when I passed my office, I saw that the torches were lit and a cupboard door was ajar! Somebody has been searching it!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote But Peeves couldn\rquote t \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote I know he couldn\rquote t, Filch!\rdblquote  Snape snapped again. \ldblquote I seal my office with a spell none but a wizard could break!\rdblquote  Snape looked up the stairs, straight through Harry, and then down into the corridor be\-low. \ldblquote I want you to come and help me search for the intruder, Filch.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote I \emdash  yes, Professor \emdash  but \emdash\rdblquote\par
Filch looked yearningly up the stairs, right through Harry, who could see that he was very reluctant to forgo the chance of corner\-ing Peeves. \i Go,\i0  Harry pleaded with him silently, \i go with Snape\i0  \'85 \i go\i0  \'85 Mrs. Norris was peering around Filch\rquote s legs. \'85 Harry had the distinct impression that she could smell him. \'85 Why had he filled that bath with so much perfumed foam?\par
\ldblquote The thing is, Professor,\rdblquote  said Filch plaintively, \ldblquote the headmaster will have to listen to me this time. Peeves has been stealing from a student, it might be my chance to get him thrown out of the castle once and for all \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Filch, I don\rquote t give a damn about that wretched poltergeist; it\rquote s my office that\rquote s \emdash\rdblquote\par
\i Clunk. Clunk. Clunk.\i0\par
Snape stopped talking very abruptly. He and Filch both looked down at the foot of the stairs. Harry saw Mad-Eye Moody limp into sight through the narrow gap between their heads. Moody was wearing his old traveling cloak over his nightshirt and leaning on his staff as usual.\par
\ldblquote Pajama party, is it?\rdblquote  he growled up the stairs.\par
\ldblquote Professor Snape and I heard noises, Professor,\rdblquote  said Filch at once. \ldblquote Peeves the Poltergeist, throwing things around as usual \emdash  and then Professor Snape discovered that someone had broken into his off \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Shut up!\rdblquote  Snape hissed to Filch.\par
Moody took a step closer to the foot of the stairs. Harry saw Moody\rquote s magical eye travel over Snape, and then, unmistakably, onto himself.\par
Harry\rquote s heart gave a horrible jolt. \i Moody could see through Invisi\-bility Cloaks\i0  \'85 he alone could see the full strangeness of the scene: Snape in his nightshirt, Filch clutching the egg, and he, Harry, trapped in the stairs behind them. Moody\rquote s lopsided gash of a mouth opened in surprise. For a few seconds, he and Harry stared straight into each other\rquote s eyes. Then Moody closed his mouth and turned his blue eye upon Snape again.\par
\ldblquote Did I hear that correctly, Snape?\rdblquote  he asked slowly. \ldblquote Someone broke into your office?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote It is unimportant,\rdblquote  said Snape coldly.\par
\ldblquote On the contrary,\rdblquote  growled Moody, \ldblquote it is very important. Who\rquote d want to break into your office?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote A student, I daresay,\rdblquote  said Snape. Harry could see a vein flick\-ering horribly on Snape\rquote s greasy temple. \ldblquote It has happened before. Potion ingredients have gone missing from my private store cup\-board \'85 students attempting illicit mixtures, no doubt. \'85\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Reckon they were after potion ingredients, eh?\rdblquote  said Moody. \ldblquote Not hiding anything else in your office, are you?\rdblquote\par
Harry saw the edge of Snape\rquote s sallow face turn a nasty brick color, the vein in his temple pulsing more rapidly.\par
\ldblquote You know I\rquote m hiding nothing, Moody,\rdblquote  he said in a soft and dangerous voice, \ldblquote as you\rquote ve searched my office pretty thoroughly yourself.\rdblquote\par
Moody\rquote s face twisted into a smile. \ldblquote Auror\rquote s privilege, Snape. Dumbledore told me to keep an eye \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Dumbledore happens to trust me,\rdblquote  said Snape through clenched teeth. \ldblquote I refuse to believe that he gave you orders to search my office!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote  \rquote Course Dumbledore trusts you,\rdblquote  growled Moody. \ldblquote He\rquote s a trusting man, isn\rquote t he? Believes in second chances. But me \emdash  I say there are spots that don\rquote t come off, Snape. Spots that never come off, d\rquote you know what I mean?\rdblquote\par
Snape suddenly did something very strange. He seized his left forearm convulsively with his right hand, as though something on it had hurt him.\par
Moody laughed. \ldblquote Get back to bed, Snape.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote You don\rquote t have the authority to send me anywhere!\rdblquote  Snape hissed, letting go of his arm as though angry with himself. \ldblquote I have as much right to prowl this school after dark as you do!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Prowl away,\rdblquote  said Moody, but his voice was full of menace. \ldblquote I look forward to meeting you in a dark corridor some time. \'85 You\rquote ve dropped something, by the way. \'85\rdblquote\par
With a stab of horror, Harry saw Moody point at the Marauder\rquote s Map, still lying on the staircase six steps below him. As Snape and Filch both turned to look at it, Harry threw caution to the winds; he raised his arms under the cloak and waved furiously at Moody to attract his attention, mouthing \ldblquote It\rquote s mine! \i Mine\i0 !\rdblquote\par
Snape had reached out for it, a horrible expression of dawning comprehension on his face \emdash\par
\ldblquote\i Accio Parchment\i0 !\rdblquote\par
The map flew up into the air, slipped through Snape\rquote s out\-stretched fingers, and soared down the stairs into Moody\rquote s hand.\par
\ldblquote My mistake,\rdblquote  Moody said calmly. \ldblquote It\rquote s mine \emdash  must\rquote ve dropped it earlier \emdash\rdblquote\par
But Snape\rquote s black eyes were darting from the egg in Filch\rquote s arms to the map in Moody\rquote s hand, and Harry could tell he was putting two and two together, as only Snape could. \'85\par
\ldblquote Potter,\rdblquote  he said quietly.\par
\ldblquote What\rquote s that?\rdblquote  said Moody calmly, folding up the map and pocketing it.\par
\ldblquote Potter!\rdblquote  Snape snarled, and he actually turned his head and stared right at the place where Harry was, as though he could sud\-denly see him. \ldblquote That egg is Potter\rquote s egg. That piece of parchment belongs to Potter. I have seen it before, I recognize it! Potter is here! Potter, in his Invisibility Cloak!\rdblquote\par
Snape stretched out his hands like a blind man and began to move up the stairs; Harry could have sworn his over-large nostrils were dilating, trying to sniff Harry out \emdash  trapped, Harry leaned backward, trying to avoid Snape\rquote s fingertips, but any moment now \emdash\par
\ldblquote There\rquote s nothing there, Snape!\rdblquote  barked Moody, \ldblquote but I\rquote ll be happy to tell the headmaster how quickly your mind jumped to Harry Potter!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Meaning what?\rdblquote  Snape turned again to look at Moody, his hands still outstretched, inches from Harry\rquote s chest.\par
\ldblquote Meaning that Dumbledore\rquote s very interested to know who\rquote s got it in for that boy!\rdblquote  said Moody, limping nearer still to the foot of the stairs. \ldblquote And so am I, Snape \'85 very interested. \'85\rdblquote  The torch\-light flickered across his mangled face, so that the scars, and the chunk missing from his nose, looked deeper and darker than ever.\par
Snape was looking down at Moody, and Harry couldn\rquote t see the expression on his face. For a moment, nobody moved or said any\-thing. Then Snape slowly lowered his hands.\par
\ldblquote I merely thought,\rdblquote  said Snape, in a voice of forced calm, \ldblquote that if Potter was wandering around after hours again \'85 it\rquote s an unfortu\-nate habit of his \'85 he should be stopped. For \emdash  for his own safety.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Ah, I see,\rdblquote  said Moody softly. \ldblquote Got Potter\rquote s best interests at heart, have you?\rdblquote\par
There was a pause. Snape and Moody were still staring at each other. Mrs. Norris gave a loud meow, still peering around Filch\rquote s legs, looking for the source of Harry\rquote s bubble-bath smell.\par
\ldblquote I think I will go back to bed,\rdblquote  Snape said curtly.\par
\ldblquote Best idea you\rquote ve had all night,\rdblquote  said Moody. \ldblquote Now, Filch, if you\rquote ll just give me that egg \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote No!\rdblquote  said Filch, clutching the egg as though it were his first\-born son. \ldblquote Professor Moody, this is evidence of Peeves\rquote  treachery!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote It\rquote s the property of the champion he stole it from,\rdblquote  said Moody. \ldblquote Hand it over, now.\rdblquote\par
Snape swept downstairs and passed Moody without another word. Filch made a chirruping noise to Mrs. Norris, who stared blankly at Harry for a few more seconds before turning and fol\-lowing her master. Still breathing very fast, Harry heard Snape walking away down the corridor; Filch handed Moody the egg and disappeared from view too, muttering to Mrs. Norris. \ldblquote Never mind, my sweet \'85 we\rquote ll see Dumbledore in the morning \'85 tell him what Peeves was up to. \'85\rdblquote\par
A door slammed. Harry was left staring down at Moody, who placed his staff on the bottommost stair and started to climb labo\-riously toward him, a dull \i clunk\i0  on every other step.\par
\ldblquote Close shave, Potter,\rdblquote  he muttered.\par
\ldblquote Yeah \'85 I \emdash  er \'85 thanks,\rdblquote  said Harry weakly.\par
\ldblquote What is this thing?\rdblquote  said Moody, drawing the Marauders Map out of his pocket and unfolding it.\par
\ldblquote Map of Hogwarts,\rdblquote  said Harry, hoping Moody was going to pull him out of the staircase soon; his leg was really hurting him.\par
\ldblquote Merlin\rquote s beard,\rdblquote  Moody whispered, staring at the map, his mag\-ical eye going haywire. \ldblquote This \'85 this is some map, Potter!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Yeah, it\rquote s \'85 quite useful,\rdblquote  Harry said. His eyes were starting to water from the pain. \ldblquote Er \emdash  Professor Moody, d\rquote you think you could help me \emdash  ?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote What? Oh! Yes \'85 yes, of course \'85\rdblquote\par
Moody took hold of Harry\rquote s arms and pulled; Harry\rquote s leg came free of the trick step, and he climbed onto the one above it. Moody was still gazing at the map.\par
\ldblquote Potter \'85\rdblquote  he said slowly, \ldblquote you didn\rquote t happen, by any chance, to see who broke into Snape\rquote s office, did you? On this map, I mean?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Er \'85 yeah, I did \'85\rdblquote  Harry admitted. \ldblquote It was Mr. Crouch.\rdblquote\par
Moody\rquote s magical eye whizzed over the entire surface of the map. He looked suddenly alarmed.\par
\ldblquote Crouch?\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote You\rquote re \emdash  you\rquote re sure, Potter?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Positive,\rdblquote  said Harry.\par
\ldblquote Well, he\rquote s not here anymore,\rdblquote  said Moody, his eye still whizzing over the map. \ldblquote Crouch \'85 that\rquote s very \emdash  very interesting. \'85\rdblquote\par
He said nothing for almost a minute, still staring at the map. Harry could tell that this news meant something to Moody and very much wanted to know what it was. He wondered whether he dared ask. Moody scared him slightly \'85 yet Moody had just helped him avoid an awful lot of trouble. \'85\par
\ldblquote Er \'85 Professor Moody \'85 why d\rquote you reckon Mr. Crouch wanted to look around Snape\rquote s office?\rdblquote\par
Moody\rquote s magical eye left the map and fixed, quivering, upon Harry. It was a penetrating glare, and Harry had the impression that Moody was sizing him up, wondering whether to answer or not, or how much to tell him.\par
\ldblquote Put it this way, Potter,\rdblquote  Moody muttered finally, \ldblquote they say old Mad-Eye\rquote s obsessed with catching Dark wizards \'85 but I\rquote m noth\-ing \emdash  \i nothing\i0  \emdash  compared to Barty Crouch.\rdblquote\par
He continued to stare at the map. Harry was burning to know more.\par
\ldblquote Professor Moody?\rdblquote  he said again. \ldblquote D\rquote you think \'85 could this have anything to do with \'85 maybe Mr. Crouch thinks there\rquote s something going on. \'85\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Like what?\rdblquote  said Moody sharply.\par
Harry wondered how much he dare say. He didn\rquote t want Moody to guess that he had a source of information outside Hogwarts; that might lead to tricky questions about Sirius.\par
\ldblquote I don\rquote t know,\rdblquote  Harry muttered, \ldblquote odd stuff\rquote s been happening lately, hasn\rquote t it? It\rquote s been in the \i Daily Prophet\i0  \'85 the Dark Mark at the World Cup, and the Death Eaters and everything. \'85\rdblquote\par
Both of Moody\rquote s mismatched eyes widened.\par
\ldblquote You\rquote re a sharp boy, Potter,\rdblquote  he said. His magical eye roved back to the Marauder\rquote s Map. \ldblquote Crouch could be thinking along those lines,\rdblquote  he said slowly. \ldblquote Very possible \'85 there have been some funny rumors flying around lately \emdash  helped along by Rita Skeeter, of course. It\rquote s making a lot of people nervous, I reckon.\rdblquote  A grim smile twisted his lopsided mouth. \ldblquote Oh if there\rquote s one thing I hate,\rdblquote  he muttered, more to himself than to Harry, and his magical eye was fixed on the left-hand corner of the map, \ldblquote it\rquote s a Death Eater who walked free. \'85\rdblquote\par
Harry stared at him. Could Moody possibly mean what Harry thought he meant?\par
\ldblquote And now I want to ask \i you\i0  a question, Potter,\rdblquote  said Moody in a more businesslike tone.\par
Harry\rquote s heart sank; he had thought this was coming. Moody was going to ask where he had got this map, which was a very dubious magical object \emdash  and the story of how it had fallen into his hands incriminated not only him, but his own father, Fred and George Weasley, and Professor Lupin, their last Defense Against the Dark Arts teacher. Moody waved the map in front of Harry, who braced himself \emdash\par
\ldblquote Can I borrow this?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Oh!\rdblquote  said Harry.\par
He was very fond of his map, but on the other hand, he was ex\-tremely relieved that Moody wasn\rquote t asking where he\rquote d got it, and there was no doubt that he owed Moody a favor.\par
\ldblquote Yeah, okay.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Good boy,\rdblquote  growled Moody. \ldblquote I can make good use of this \'85 this might be \i exactly\i0  what I\rquote ve been looking for. \'85 Right, bed, Potter, come on, now. \'85\rdblquote\par
They climbed to the top of the stairs together, Moody still ex\-amining the map as though it was a treasure the like of which he had never seen before. They walked in silence to the door of Moody\rquote s office, where he stopped and looked up at Harry.\par
\ldblquote You ever thought of a career as an Auror, Potter?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Harry, taken aback.\par
\ldblquote You want to consider it,\rdblquote  said Moody, nodding and looking at Harry thoughtfully. \ldblquote Yes, indeed \'85 and incidentally \'85 I\rquote m guessing you weren\rquote t just taking that egg for a walk tonight?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Er \emdash  no,\rdblquote  said Harry, grinning. \ldblquote I\rquote ve been working out the clue.\rdblquote\par
Moody winked at him, his magical eye going haywire again.\par
\ldblquote Nothing like a nighttime stroll to give you ideas, Potter. \'85 See you in the morning. \'85\rdblquote\par
He went back into his office, staring down at the Marauder\rquote s Map again, and closed the door behind him.\par
Harry walked slowly back to Gryffindor Tower, lost in thought about Snape, and Crouch, and what it all meant. \'85 Why was Crouch pretending to be ill, if he could manage to get to Hogwarts when he wanted to? What did he think Snape was concealing in his office?\par
And Moody thought he, Harry, ought to be an Auror! Interest\-ing idea \'85 but somehow, Harry thought, as he got quietly into his four-poster ten minutes later, the egg and the cloak now safely back in his trunk, he thought he\rquote d like to check how scarred the rest of them were before he chose it as a career.\par
