Harry, Ron, and Hermione went up to the Owlery after breakfast on Sunday to send a letter to Percy, asking, as Sirius had suggested, whether he had seen Mr. Crouch lately. They used Hedwig, because it had been so long since she\rquote d had a job. When they had watched her fly out of sight through the Owlery window, they proceeded down to the kitchen to give Dobby his new socks.\par
The house-elves gave them a very cheery welcome, bowing and curtsying and bustling around making tea again. Dobby was ecsta\-tic about his present.\par
\ldblquote Harry Potter is too good to Dobby!\rdblquote  he squeaked, wiping large tears out of his enormous eyes.\par
\ldblquote You saved my life with that gillyweed, Dobby, you really did,\rdblquote  said Harry.\par
\ldblquote No chance of more of those eclairs, is there?\rdblquote  said Ron, who was looking around at the beaming and bowing house-elves.\par
\ldblquote You\rquote ve just had breakfast!\rdblquote  said Hermione irritably, but a great silver platter of eclairs was already zooming toward them, sup\-ported by four elves.\par
\ldblquote We should get some stuff to send up to Snuffles,\rdblquote  Harry muttered.\par
\ldblquote Good idea,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote Give Pig something to do. You couldn\rquote t give us a bit of extra food, could you?\rdblquote  he said to the surrounding elves, and they bowed delightedly and hurried off to get some more.\par
\ldblquote Dobby, where\rquote s Winky?\rdblquote  said Hermione, who was looking around.\par
\ldblquote Winky is over there by the fire, miss,\rdblquote  said Dobby quietly, his ears drooping slightly.\par
\ldblquote Oh dear,\rdblquote  said Hermione as she spotted Winky.\par
Harry looked over at the fireplace too. Winky was sitting on the same stool as last time, but she had allowed herself to become so filthy that she was not immediately distinguishable from the smoke-blackened brick behind her. Her clothes were ragged and unwashed. She was clutching a bottle of butterbeer and swaying slightly on her stool, staring into the fire. As they watched her, she gave an enormous hiccup.\par
\ldblquote Winky is getting through six bottles a day now,\rdblquote  Dobby whis\-pered to Harry.\par
\ldblquote Well, it\rquote s not strong, that stuff,\rdblquote  Harry said.\par
But Dobby shook his head. \ldblquote  \rquote Tis strong for a house-elf, sir,\rdblquote  he said.\par
Winky hiccuped again. The elves who had brought the eclairs gave her disapproving looks as they returned to work.\par
\ldblquote Winky is pining,  Harry Potter,\rdblquote   Dobby whispered sadly. \ldblquote Winky wants to go home. Winky still thinks Mr. Crouch is her master, sir, and nothing Dobby says will persuade her that Profes\-sor Dumbledore is her master now.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Hey, Winky,\rdblquote  said Harry, struck by a sudden inspiration, walk\-ing over to her, and bending down, \ldblquote you don\rquote t know what Mr. Crouch might be up to, do you? Because he\rquote s stopped turning up to judge the Triwizard Tournament.\rdblquote\par
Winky\rquote s eyes flickered. Her enormous pupils focused on Harry. She swayed slightly again and then said, \ldblquote M \emdash  Master is stopped \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  coming?\rdblquote\par
