Winky swayed some more, staring blurrily at Harry.\par
\ldblquote Master \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  ill?\rdblquote\par
Her bottom lip began to tremble.\par
\ldblquote But we\rquote re not sure if that\rquote s true,\rdblquote  said Hermione quickly.\par
\ldblquote Master is needing his \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  Winky!\rdblquote  whimpered the elf. \ldblquote Master cannot \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  manage \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  all by himself. \'85\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Other people manage to do their own housework, you know, Winky,\rdblquote  Hermione said severely.\par
\ldblquote Winky \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  is not only \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  doing housework for Mr. Crouch!\rdblquote  Winky squeaked indignantly, swaying worse than ever and slopping butterbeer down her already heavily stained blouse. \ldblquote Master is \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  trusting Winky with \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  the most important \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  the most secret \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  said Harry.\par
But Winky shook her head very hard, spilling more butterbeer down herself.\par
\ldblquote Winky keeps \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  her master\rquote s secrets,\rdblquote  she said muti\-nously, swaying very heavily now, frowning up at Harry with her eyes crossed. \ldblquote You is \emdash  \i hi\i0 c\i  \i0\emdash  nosing, you is.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Winky must not talk like that to Harry Potter!\rdblquote  said Dobby an\-grily. \ldblquote Harry Potter is brave and noble and Harry Potter is not nosy!\par
\ldblquote He is nosing \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  into my master\rquote s \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  private and secret \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  Winky is a good house-elf \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  Winky keeps her silence \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  people trying to \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash  pry and poke \emdash  \i hic\i0  \emdash\rdblquote\par
Winky\rquote s eyelids drooped and suddenly, without warning, she slid off her stool into the hearth, snoring loudly. The empty bottle of butterbeer rolled away across the stone-flagged floor. Half a dozen house-elves came hurrying forward, looking disgusted. One of them picked up the bottle; the others covered Winky with a large checked tablecloth and tucked the ends in neatly, hiding her from view.\par
\ldblquote We is sorry you had to see that, sirs and miss!\rdblquote  squeaked a nearby elf, shaking his head and looking very ashamed. \ldblquote We is hop\-ing you will not judge us all by Winky, sirs and miss!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote She\rquote s unhappy!\rdblquote  said Hermione, exasperated. \ldblquote Why don\rquote t you try and cheer her up instead of covering her up?\rdblquote\par
