The house-elves crowded around Harry, Ron, and Hermione and began shunting them out of the kitchen, many little hands pushing in the smalls of their backs.\par
\ldblquote Thank you for the socks, Harry Potter!\rdblquote  Dobby called miser\-ably from the hearth, where he was standing next to the lumpy tablecloth that was Winky.\par
\ldblquote You couldn\rquote t keep your mouth shut, could you, Hermione?\rdblquote  said Ron angrily as the kitchen door slammed shut behind them. \ldblquote They won\rquote t want us visiting them now! We could\rquote ve tried to get more stuff out of Winky about Crouch!\rdblquote\par
