BeTteR. GO back wherE you cAMe from mUGgle.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj\par
\ldblquote They\rquote re all like it!\rdblquote  said Hermione desperately, opening one let\-ter after another. \ldblquote  \lquote\i Harry Potter can do much better than the likes of you. \'85\i0\rquote  \lquote\i You deserve to be boiled in frog spawn\i0 . \'85\rquote  Ouch!\rdblquote\par
She had opened the last envelope, and yellowish-green liquid smelling strongly of petrol gushed over her hands, which began to erupt in large yellow boils.\par
\ldblquote Undiluted bubotuber pus!\rdblquote  said Ron, picking up the envelope gingerly and sniffing it.\par
\ldblquote Ow!\rdblquote  said Hermione, tears starting in her eyes as she tried to rub the pus off her hands with a napkin, but her fingers were now so thickly covered in painful sores that it looked as though she were wearing a pair of thick, knobbly gloves.\par
\ldblquote You\rquote d better get up to the hospital wing,\rdblquote  said Harry as the owls around Hermione took flight. \ldblquote We\rquote ll tell Professor Sprout where you\rquote ve gone. \'85\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote I warned her!\rdblquote  said Ron as Hermione hurried out of the Great Hall, cradling her hands. \ldblquote I warned her not to annoy Rita Skeeter! Look at this one \'85\rdblquote  He read out one of the letters Hermione had left behind: \ldblquote  \lquote\i I read in\i0  Witch Weekly \i about how you are playing Harry Potter false and that boy has had enough hardship and I will be sending you a curse by next post as soon as I can find a big enough en\-velope.\i0\rquote  Blimey, she\rquote d better watch out for herself.\rdblquote\par
Hermione didn\rquote t turn up for Herbology. As Harry and Ron left the greenhouse for their Care of Magical Creatures class, they saw Malfoy, Crabbe, and Goyle descending the stone steps of the castle. Pansy Parkinson was whispering and giggling behind them with her gang of Slytherin girls. Catching sight of Harry, Pansy called, \ldblquote Potter, have you split up with your girlfriend? Why was she so up\-set at breakfast?\rdblquote\par
Harry ignored her; he didn\rquote t want to give her the satisfaction of knowing how much trouble the \i Witch Weekly\i0  article had caused.\par
Hagrid, who had told them last lesson that they had finished with unicorns, was waiting for them outside his cabin with a fresh supply of open crates at his feet. Harry\rquote s heart sank at the sight of the crates \emdash  surely not another skrewt hatching? \emdash  but when he got near enough to see inside, he found himself looking at a num\-ber of fluffy black creatures with long snouts. Their front paws were curiously flat, like spades, and they were blinking up at the class, looking politely puzzled at all the attention.\par
