\ldblquote Hang on,\rdblquote  said Hagrid, looking down into the crate, \ldblquote there\rquote s a spare niffler here \'85 who\rquote s missin\rquote ? Where\rquote s Hermione?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote She had to go to the hospital wing,\rdblquote  said Ron.\par
\ldblquote We\rquote ll explain later,\rdblquote  Harry muttered; Pansy Parkinson was listening.\par
It was easily the most fun they had ever had in Care of Magical Creatures. The nifflers dived in and out of the patch of earth as though it were water, each scurrying back to the student who had released it and spitting gold into their hands. Ron\rquote s was particularly efficient; it had soon filled his lap with coins.\par
\ldblquote Can you buy these as pets, Hagrid?\rdblquote  he asked excitedly as his niffler dived back into the soil, splattering his robes.\par
\ldblquote Yer mum wouldn\rquote  be happy, Ron,\rdblquote  said Hagrid, grinning. \ldblquote They wreck houses, nifflers. I reckon they\rquote ve nearly got the lot, now,\rdblquote  he added, pacing around the patch of earth while the nifflers continued to dive. \ldblquote I on\rquote y buried a hundred coins. Oh there y\rquote are, Hermione!\rdblquote\par
Hermione was walking toward them across the lawn. Her hands were very heavily bandaged and she looked miserable. Pansy Parkinson was watching her beadily.\par
\ldblquote Well, let\rquote s check how yeh\rquote ve done!\rdblquote  said Hagrid. \ldblquote Count yer coins! An\rquote  there\rquote s no point tryin\rquote  ter steal any, Goyle,\rdblquote  he added, his beetle-black eyes narrowed. \ldblquote It\rquote s leprechaun gold. Vanishes after a few hours.\rdblquote\par
Goyle emptied his pockets, looking extremely sulky. It turned out that Ron\rquote s niffler had been most successful, so Hagrid gave him an enormous slab of Honeydukes chocolate for a prize. The bell rang across the grounds for lunch; the rest of the class set off back to the castle, but Harry, Ron, and Hermione stayed behind to help Hagrid put the nifflers back in their boxes. Harry noticed Madame Maxime watching them out of her carriage window.\par
\ldblquote What yeh done ter your hands, Hermione?\rdblquote  said Hagrid, look\-ing concerned.\par
Hermione told him about the hate mail she had received that morning, and the envelope full of bubotuber pus.\par
\ldblquote Aaah, don\rquote  worry,\rdblquote  said Hagrid gently, looking down at her. \ldblquote I got some o\rquote  those letters an\rquote  all, after Rita Skeeter wrote abou\rquote  me mum. \lquote\i Yeh\rquote re a monster an\rquote  yeh should be put down\i0 .\rquote  \lquote\i Yer mother killed innocent people an\rquote  if you had any decency you\rquote d jump in a lake.\i0\rquote  \rdblquote\par
\ldblquote No!\rdblquote  said Hermione, looking shocked.\par
\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Hagrid, heaving the niffler crates over by his cabin wall. \ldblquote They\rquote re jus\rquote  nutters, Hermione. Don\rquote  open \rquote em if yeh get any more. Chuck \rquote em straigh\rquote  in the fire.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote You missed a really good lesson,\rdblquote  Harry told Hermione as they headed back toward the castle. \ldblquote They\rquote re good, nifflers, aren\rquote t they, Ron?\rdblquote\par
Ron, however, was frowning at the chocolate Hagrid had given him. He looked thoroughly put out about something.\par
\ldblquote What\rquote s the matter?\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Wrong flavor?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Ron shortly. \ldblquote Why didn\rquote t you tell me about the gold?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote What gold?\rdblquote  said Harry.\par
\ldblquote The gold I gave you at the Quidditch World Cup,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote The leprechaun gold I gave you for my Omnioculars. In the Top Box. Why didn\rquote t you tell me it disappeared?\rdblquote\par
Harry had to think for a moment before he realized what Ron was talking about.\par
\ldblquote Oh \'85\rdblquote  he said, the memory coming back to him at last. \ldblquote I dunno \'85 I never noticed it had gone. I was more worried about my wand, wasn\rquote t I?\rdblquote\par
They climbed the steps into the entrance hall and went into the Great Hall for lunch.\par
\ldblquote Must be nice,\rdblquote  Ron said abruptly, when they had sat down and started serving themselves roast beef and Yorkshire puddings. \ldblquote To have so much money you don\rquote t notice if a pocketful of Galleons goes missing.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Listen, I had other stuff on my mind that night!\rdblquote  said Harry impatiently. \ldblquote We all did, remember?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote I didn\rquote t know leprechaun gold vanishes,\rdblquote  Ron muttered. \ldblquote I thought I was paying you back. You shouldn\rquote t\rquote ve given me that Chudley Cannon hat for Christmas.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Forget it, all right?\rdblquote  said Harry.\par
Ron speared a roast potato on the end of his fork, glaring at it. Then he said, \ldblquote I hate being poor.\rdblquote\par
Harry and Hermione looked at each other. Neither of them re\-ally knew what to say.\par
\ldblquote It\rquote s rubbish,\rdblquote  said Ron, still glaring down at his potato. \ldblquote I don\rquote t blame Fred and George for trying to make some extra money. Wish I could. Wish I had a niffler.\rdblquote\par
