\pard\nowidctlpar\qc Priori Incantatem\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj\fs20\par
Wormtail approached Harry, who scrambled to find his feet, to support his own weight before the ropes were un\-tied. Wormtail raised his new silver hand, pulled out the wad of material gagging Harry, and then, with one swipe, cut through the bonds tying Harry to the gravestone.\par
There was a split second, perhaps, when Harry might have con\-sidered running for it, but his injured leg shook under him as he stood on the overgrown grave, as the Death Eaters closed ranks, forming a tighter circle around him and Voldemort, so that the gaps where the missing Death Eaters should have stood were filled. Wormtail walked out of the circle to the place where Cedric\rquote s body lay and returned with Harry\rquote s wand, which he thrust roughly into Harry\rquote s hand without looking at him. Then Wormtail resumed his place in the circle of watching Death Eaters.\par
\ldblquote You have been taught how to duel, Harry Potter?\rdblquote  said Volde\-mort softly, his red eyes glinting through the darkness.\par
At these words Harry remembered, as though from a former life, the dueling club at Hogwarts he had attended briefly two years ago. \'85 All he had learned there was the Disarming Spell, \ldblquote\i Expel\-liarmus\i0\rdblquote  \'85 and what use would it be to deprive Voldemort of his wand, even if he could, when he was surrounded by Death Eaters, outnumbered by at least thirty to one? He had never learned any\-thing that could possibly fit him for this. He knew he was facing the thing against which Moody had always warned \'85 the un-blockable \i Avada Kedavra\i0  curse \emdash  and Voldemort was right \emdash  his mother was not here to die for him this time. \'85 He was quite unprotected. \'85\par
\ldblquote We bow to each other, Harry,\rdblquote  said Voldemort, bending a little, but keeping his snakelike face upturned to Harry. \ldblquote Come, the niceties must be observed. \'85 Dumbledore would like you to show manners. \'85 Bow to death, Harry. \'85\rdblquote\par
The Death Eaters were laughing again. Voldemort\rquote s lipless mouth was smiling. Harry did not bow. He was not going to let Voldemort play with him before killing him \'85 he was not going to give him that satisfaction. \'85\par
\ldblquote I said, \i bow,\i0\rdblquote  Voldemort said, raising his wand \emdash  and Harry felt his spine curve as though a huge, invisible hand were bending him ruthlessly forward, and the Death Eaters laughed harder than ever.\par
\ldblquote Very good,\rdblquote  said Voldemort softly, and as he raised his wand the pressure bearing down upon Harry lifted too. \ldblquote And now you face me, like a man \'85 straight-backed and proud, the way your father died. \'85\par
